      <div class="job">
        <div class="title">RF Integrated Passive Device (RFIPD) Intern Engineer</div>
        <div class="company">Skyworks Solutions, Inc., Irvine, CA, USA</div>
        <div class="date">May 2024 – Aug. 2024</div>
        <ul>
          <li>Researched efficient methods for inductor miniaturization using ferrite materials.</li>
          <li>Integrated inductors in RF modules for cellular applications.</li>
          <li>Work resulted in a patent.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <hr />

      <div class="job">
        <div class="title">Graduate Research Assistant (Annenberg Fellow)</div>
        <div class="company">University of Southern California, Los Angeles, CA, USA</div>
        <div class="date">Aug. 2021 – Present</div>
        <ul>
          <li>Designed LNAs, Mixers, Wideband IF amplifiers, Filters, Launchers, and Antennas for RFIC and Sub-THz systems.</li>
          <li>Developed a full D-band (110–170 GHz) receiver using TSMC 28nm CMOS technology.</li>
          <li>Collaborated with Intel on low-dispersion dielectric waveguide techniques, including packaging and calibration.</li>
          <li>Proposed efficient concurrent dual-mode excitation methods for SIWs and half-mode SIWs.</li>
          <li>Proposed a novel dual-mode SIW-based coupler.</li>
          <li>Experienced with R&S VNA (ZVA50), frequency extenders, and RF probing tools.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <hr />

      <div class="job">
        <div class="title">Software Development Engineer – Device Modeling (R&D)</div>
        <div class="company">Siemens Digital Industries (Mentor Graphics), Cairo, Egypt</div>
        <div class="date">Sep. 2018 – July 2021</div>
        <ul>
          <li>Participated in 11 software release cycles, implementing ~3 models per cycle.</li>
          <li>Led the implementation and testing of the Advanced Spice Model for GaN HEMT (ASM-HEMT).</li>
          <li>Conducted research on RF simulation impacts on semiconductor device models.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <hr />

      <div class="job">
        <div class="title">Research Assistant – Microwave and Antenna Research Lab</div>
        <div class="company">Ain Shams University, Cairo, Egypt</div>
        <div class="date">Sep. 2017 – July 2021</div>
        <ul>
          <li>Proposed and modeled a multi-mode star-junction for miniaturized couplers; published in IMS.</li>
          <li>Extended star-junction for microstrip/slotline applications; presented at EuMC.</li>
          <li>Submitted research on differential couplers with wide bandwidth and enhanced CMRR to IEEE MTT.</li>
          <li>Explored Butler Matrix augmentation using junctions for phased arrays.</li>
          <li>Hands-on with ANSYS HFSS, Designer, Anritsu MS4647A (70 GHz) VNA, and antenna chamber measurements.</li>
          <li>Co-authored: “SETB Microstrip/Slotline Rat-race Coupler with Wideband CM Suppression” (under review at IEEE MTT).</li>
